  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Double wall oven service — why we maintain it as its own discipline</h2>
    <p>Electrolux double wall oven repair is a distinct diagnostic category from single wall oven repair, and that's not just marketing — it reflects the actual cavity-independent architecture. The upper and lower cavities are fully independent cooking units with their own bake element, broil element, thermal sensor, convection components (on convection-equipped tiers), and cavity-specific control relays. They share the main control board, user interface, cooling fan, and door lock circuit. This matters for four reasons our diagnostic approach addresses:</p>
    <p><b>1. Failure-isolation pattern identification.</b> Upper bake fails but lower bakes fine isolates the failure to upper-cavity components — we test and quote only those. Customers who get quoted for "double wall oven repair" at blanket 2× pricing are being overquoted by service that hasn't done the isolation work.</p>
    <p><b>2. Pyrolytic + self-clean sequencing.</b> Double wall ovens with self-clean often only allow one cavity to run self-clean at a time (thermal load management). If self-clean works in upper cavity but not lower, the isolation points to lower-cavity door lock or lower-cavity thermal safety circuit, not a universal self-clean failure.</p>
    <p><b>3. Parts stocking honesty.</b> We carry cavity-specific thermal sensors + bake elements for both common Electrolux double wall oven generations; shared components (main control board, user interface) are ordered on demand since generation-specific variants don't stock well. Lead time transparency at diagnostic.</p>
    <p><b>4. LA installation access.</b> Double wall oven units in LA custom kitchens frequently have tight cabinet reveal + wall-mounted installations that restrict rear access for certain component changes. We assess installation access at diagnostic before committing a repair timeline — some double wall oven service requires partial slide-out of the unit, which changes the service duration.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Electrolux vs Frigidaire vs Icon Professional — LA buyer disambiguation</h2>
    <p><b>Electrolux mainstream (this page)</b> — Swedish-engineered premium tier, Frigidaire-shared chassis on mainstream, distinct IQ-Touch capacitive control + Luxury-Glide rack signatures. 2-4 day parts from Electrolux USA.</p>
    <p><b>Frigidaire</b> — Same parent (Electrolux AB since 1986), positioned as mainstream-to-value tier. Gallery + Professional sub-tiers. Much of the chassis is shared with mainstream Electrolux. See <a href="/brands/frigidaire-oven-repair/">Frigidaire oven repair</a>.</p>
    <p><b>Icon Professional (legacy)</b> — Discontinued 2017 Electrolux pro-style sub-brand; still serviceable on 2005-2017 build years. Separate parts chain, 5-10 day lead, 25-40% service premium over mainstream Electrolux.</p>
    <p>Choice drivers: Electrolux mainstream for Swedish-engineered premium without Icon premium; Frigidaire for equivalent Electrolux-shared-chassis engineering at mainstream price point; Icon for households that inherited 2005-2017 pro-style installs and need factory-pattern service.</p>
  </div></section>

